dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures. Prime meridian: London. "Entered according to Act of Congress in the year 1855, by J.H. Colton & Co. ..." "Grid in miles from the General Post Office." "No. 108." Text on verso: Palestine - Kingdom of Iran, or Persia, p. 109. 1 map: col.; 30 x 37 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
